Money Stuff =0A A plausible model of traders at big investment banks might =
be: They are =0Aplaying a game of poker with their customers, in which they=
 selectiv =0A=0A=0A =0A<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/authors/ARbTQlRLR=
jE/matthew-s-levine=3Fcmpid=3DBBD120424_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_s=
ource=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=3D241204&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystuff>=0A =0A<http=
s://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D11917799&m=3D2=
1d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D12042024>=0A=0A=0A=0ACiti sales traders=
=0A=0AA plausible model of traders at big investment banks might be:=0A=0A =
* They are playing a game of poker with their customers, in which they =0As=
electively use and withhold information in order to make the bank more mone=
y. =0A(And the customers do the same to them.) =0A * Some of the stuff that=
